<TITLE> CVC, Blackstone bid for joint M&B stake:sources </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 LONDON, April 10 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Private equity firms CVC Capital Partners and Blackstone made a joint bid to buy a stake of up to 29.9 percent in restaurant and pub firm Mitchells & Butlers, people close to the matter said on Thursday. One of the sources said buyout firms Permira and Bain Capital were also interested in the group, which is up for sale. The Times reported that Permira had made a similar offer to that made by Blackstone and CVC, while Bain Capital was also mulling a stake purchase. The newspaper said part of the stakes could be taken in the form of convertible securities and lead to the private equity firms having representation on M&B's board. A Blackstone spokeswoman declined to comment, while nobody was immediately available for comment at M&B, CVC, Permira or Bain. Shares in M&B were up 1.33 percent at 322.75 pence at 1027 G
